# Package Boundary Rules

## Dependency Chain

Packages must only import **downward** in this chain:

```
@excalidraw/common
  ↓
@excalidraw/math
  ↓
@excalidraw/element
  ↓
@excalidraw/excalidraw
  ↓
excalidraw-app
```

`@excalidraw/utils` is a leaf utility package — any package may import from it.

## Rules

- **`@excalidraw/common`** — no imports from `@excalidraw/element`, `@excalidraw/excalidraw`, or `excalidraw-app`.
- **`@excalidraw/math`** — may import from `@excalidraw/common` only.
- **`@excalidraw/element`** — may import from `@excalidraw/common`, `@excalidraw/math`, and `@excalidraw/utils`. Importing from `@excalidraw/excalidraw` is **forbidden for new code** (existing `import type` from `@excalidraw/excalidraw/types` is known tech debt — do not add more).
- **`@excalidraw/excalidraw`** — may import from all packages above. Must NOT import from `excalidraw-app`.
- **`excalidraw-app`** — may import from all packages. Nothing imports from `excalidraw-app`.

## Known Tech Debt

`packages/element/src/` contains `import type { AppState, ... } from "@excalidraw/excalidraw/types"` in several files. These are type-only upward imports and are tracked as tech debt. **Do not add new ones.** If you need a type from `excalidraw`, move it to `packages/element/src/types.ts` or `packages/common/src/` instead.

## How to Verify

```bash
# Detect new upward imports from element → excalidraw (value imports, not just types)
grep -rn "^import [^t].*from \"@excalidraw/excalidraw" packages/element/src/ --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"
# Expected: no output (type-only imports with `import type` are tolerated as existing debt)

# Detect any imports from excalidraw-app inside packages
grep -rn "from \".*excalidraw-app" packages/ --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"
# Expected: no output

# Detect imports from element or excalidraw inside common
grep -rn "from \"@excalidraw/element\|from \"@excalidraw/excalidraw" packages/common/src/ --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"
# Expected: no output

# Detect imports from element or excalidraw inside math
grep -rn "from \"@excalidraw/element\|from \"@excalidraw/excalidraw" packages/math/src/ --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"
# Expected: no output
```
